<tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-above" style="font-size:125%;"><div class="fn">Alfredo Castillero Hoyos</div></th></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" class="infobox-full-data"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1257001546"></td></tr>
<tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-header">Academic background</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Education</th>
<td class="infobox-data">
<a href="/wiki/University_of_Warwick" title="University of Warwick">University of Warwick</a> (<a href="/wiki/Master_of_Arts" title="Master of Arts">MA</a>)<br><a href="/wiki/University_of_Portsmouth" title="University of Portsmouth">University of Portsmouth</a> (<a href="/wiki/PhD" class="mw-redirect" title="PhD">PhD</a>)</td>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1257001546">
</tr>
<tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-header">Academic work</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Discipline</th>
<td class="infobox-data"><a href="/wiki/Political_science" title="Political science">Political science</a></td>
</tr>
<tr style="display:none"><td colspan="2">
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<p><b>Alfredo Castillero Hoyos</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Panamanian" class="mw-redirect" title="Panamanian">Panamanian</a> <a href="/wiki/Political_scientist" class="mw-redirect" title="Political scientist">political scientist</a>, human rights <a href="/wiki/Activist" class="mw-redirect" title="Activist">activist</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Professor" title="Professor">professor</a>. He was a member of the <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Human_Rights_Committee" class="mw-redirect" title="Human Rights Committee">Human Rights Committee</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and ran for the ombudsman office of <a href="/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a>.
</p>
<p>Alfredo Castillero Hoyos graduated at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Warwick" title="University of Warwick">University of Warwick</a> where he obtained a master's degree in political studied in 1993. He then went on to complete post-graduate studies in the methodology of social sciences and a doctorate in political studies, both at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Portsmouth" title="University of Portsmouth">University of Portsmouth</a> in 1999.
</p>
